<Layout title="Dist Ch.8 — Distributed Transactions" favicon="🌐">
  <main>

    <a href="/reading/distributed-systems/" class="text-sm mb-4 inline-block">&larr; back to distributed systems</a>

    <h1>Distributed Transactions</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mb-6">Wikipedia &middot; <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Two-phase_commit_protocol"><img src="/reading/wikipedia.svg" alt="wp" style="display:inline;height:1em;vertical-align:-0.1em;margin-right:0.2em;"/>Two-phase commit</a></p>

    <div class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-5 mb-8 callout">
      <p class="text-lg" style="max-width:none"><strong>Two-phase commit (2PC)</strong> ensures all-or-nothing across multiple nodes. Phase 1: coordinator asks participants to prepare (vote yes/no). Phase 2: if all vote yes, coordinator commits; otherwise aborts. The weakness: if the coordinator crashes after prepare, participants are stuck waiting. Sagas offer an alternative: execute steps with compensating actions for rollback.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- SVG: 2PC coordinator/participant protocol -->
    <div class="flex justify-center my-6">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 420 280" class="w-full max-w-md" style="font-family: ui-monospace, monospace;">
        <!-- Coordinator timeline -->
        <line x1="100" y1="30" x2="100" y2="260" stroke="#60a5fa" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-opacity="0.4"/>
        <text x="100" y="20" text-anchor="middle" fill="#60a5fa" font-size="11">Coordinator</text>
        <!-- Participant 1 timeline -->
        <line x1="250" y1="30" x2="250" y2="260" stroke="#34d399" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-opacity="0.4"/>
        <text x="250" y="20" text-anchor="middle" fill="#34d399" font-size="11">Participant 1</text>
        <!-- Participant 2 timeline -->
        <line x1="360" y1="30" x2="360" y2="260" stroke="#f59e0b" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-opacity="0.4"/>
        <text x="360" y="20" text-anchor="middle" fill="#f59e0b" font-size="11">Participant 2</text>
        <!-- Phase 1: prepare -->
        <text x="40" y="55" fill="currentColor" font-size="9" fill-opacity="0.5">Phase 1</text>
        <line x1="104" y1="50" x2="246" y2="70" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1" stroke-opacity="0.4"/>
        <text x="170" y="55" fill="currentColor" font-size="8" fill-opacity="0.5">prepare?</text>
        <line x1="104" y1="50" x2="356" y2="75" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1" stroke-opacity="0.4"/>
        <!-- Vote yes -->
        <line x1="246" y1="90" x2="104" y2="110" stroke="#34d399" stroke-width="1" stroke-opacity="0.4"/>
        <text x="170" y="95" fill="#34d399" font-size="8" fill-opacity="0.7">yes</text>
        <line x1="356" y1="95" x2="104" y2="115" stroke="#f59e0b" stroke-width="1" stroke-opacity="0.4"/>
        <text x="230" y="100" fill="#f59e0b" font-size="8" fill-opacity="0.7">yes</text>
        <!-- Phase 2: commit -->
        <text x="40" y="150" fill="currentColor" font-size="9" fill-opacity="0.5">Phase 2</text>
        <line x1="104" y1="145" x2="246" y2="165" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1" stroke-opacity="0.4"/>
        <text x="170" y="150" fill="currentColor" font-size="8" fill-opacity="0.5">commit!</text>
        <line x1="104" y1="145" x2="356" y2="170" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1" stroke-opacity="0.4"/>
        <!-- Ack -->
        <line x1="246" y1="185" x2="104" y2="205" stroke="#34d399" stroke-width="1" stroke-opacity="0.4"/>
        <text x="170" y="192" fill="#34d399" font-size="8" fill-opacity="0.7">ack</text>
        <line x1="356" y1="190" x2="104" y2="210" stroke="#f59e0b" stroke-width="1" stroke-opacity="0.4"/>
        <text x="230" y="197" fill="#f59e0b" font-size="8" fill-opacity="0.7">ack</text>
        <!-- Done -->
        <circle cx="100" cy="230" r="3" fill="#34d399"/>
        <text x="100" y="250" text-anchor="middle" fill="currentColor" font-size="9" fill-opacity="0.5">done</text>
      </svg>
    </div>

    <!-- 1. 2PC -->
    <h3>Two-phase commit</h3>

    <SchemeRepl client:visible initialCode={`; Two-phase commit simulation.
; Phase 1: coordinator asks, participants vote.
; Phase 2: if all yes, commit. Otherwise abort.

(define (two-phase-commit votes)
  (display "Phase 1: collecting votes") (newline)
  (let loop ((v votes) (i 1))
    (if (null? v) #t
        (begin
          (display "  Participant ") (display i) (display ": ")
          (display (if (car v) "YES" "NO")) (newline)
          (loop (cdr v) (+ i 1)))))

  (display "Phase 2: ")
  (let ((all-yes (let loop ((v votes))
                   (if (null? v) #t
                       (and (car v) (loop (cdr v)))))))
    (if all-yes
        (display "COMMIT")
        (display "ABORT"))
    (newline)))

(display "--- All agree ---") (newline)
(two-phase-commit (list #t #t #t))
(newline)
(display "--- One votes no ---") (newline)
(two-phase-commit (list #t #f #t))
`} />

    <!-- 2. The blocking problem -->
    <h3>The blocking problem</h3>
    <p>If the coordinator crashes after sending prepare but before sending commit/abort, participants that voted yes are <strong>blocked</strong>. They cannot commit (the coordinator might abort) or abort (the coordinator might commit). They must wait. This is why 2PC is called a <strong>blocking protocol</strong>. Three-phase commit (3PC) adds a pre-commit phase to reduce blocking, but is more complex and still not partition-tolerant.</p>

    <!-- 3. Saga pattern -->
    <h3>Saga pattern</h3>
    <p>A <strong>saga</strong> splits a distributed transaction into a sequence of local transactions. Each step has a <strong>compensating transaction</strong> that undoes its effects. If step 3 fails, run compensations for steps 2 and 1 in reverse. No coordinator lock. No blocking. The tradeoff: intermediate states are visible (no isolation).</p>

    <SchemeRepl client:visible initialCode={`; Saga pattern: forward steps + compensating actions.
; If a step fails, run compensations in reverse.

(define steps (list "reserve hotel" "book flight" "charge card"))
(define compensations (list "cancel hotel" "cancel flight" "refund card"))

(define (run-saga steps compensations fail-at)
  (let loop ((s steps) (c compensations) (i 1) (done (list)))
    (if (null? s)
        (begin (display "Saga completed successfully") (newline))
        (if (= i fail-at)
            (begin
              (display "Step ") (display i) (display " FAILED: ")
              (display (car s)) (newline)
              (display "Running compensations:") (newline)
              (let undo ((d (reverse done)))
                (if (null? d) #t
                    (begin
                      (display "  ") (display (car d)) (newline)
                      (undo (cdr d))))))
            (begin
              (display "Step ") (display i) (display ": ")
              (display (car s)) (newline)
              (loop (cdr s) (cdr c) (+ i 1)
                    (cons (car c) done)))))))

(display "--- Success ---") (newline)
(run-saga steps compensations 99)
(newline)
(display "--- Fail at step 3 ---") (newline)
(run-saga steps compensations 3)
`} />

    <div class="python-block my-2" style="display:none">
      <Repl client:visible initialCode={`# Saga pattern
steps = ["reserve hotel", "book flight", "charge card"]
compensations = ["cancel hotel", "cancel flight", "refund card"]

def run_saga(fail_at=None):
    done = []
    for i, (step, comp) in enumerate(zip(steps, compensations)):
        if i == fail_at:
            print(f"Step {i+1} FAILED: {step}")
            print("Running compensations:")
            for c in reversed(done):
                print(f"  {c}")
            return
        print(f"Step {i+1}: {step}")
        done.append(comp)
    print("Saga completed successfully")

print("--- Success ---")
run_saga()
print("\\n--- Fail at step 3 ---")
run_saga(fail_at=2)
`} />
